.TH "cifs_backup_query_path_info" 9 "cifs_backup_query_path_info" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cifs_backup_query_path_info \- SMB1 fallback code to get ino
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cifs_backup_query_path_info
.BI "(int xid "  ","
.BI "struct cifs_tcon *tcon "  ","
.BI "struct super_block *sb "  ","
.BI "const char *full_path "  ","
.BI "void **resp_buf "  ","
.BI "FILE_ALL_INFO **data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "xid" 12
transaction id used to identify original request in logs
.IP "tcon" 12
information about the server share we have mounted
.IP "sb" 12
the superblock stores info such as disk space available
.IP "full_path" 12
name of the file we are getting the metadata for
.IP "resp_buf" 12
will be set to cifs resp buf and needs to be freed with
\fBcifs_buf_release\fP when done with \fIdata\fP
.IP "data" 12
will be set to search info result buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Fallback code to get file metadata when we don't have access to
full_path (EACCES) and have backup creds.
